   {
    "titre": "Incorporate the Butter",
    "detail": "Add the soft butter in pieces gradually. Knead for 10 minutes by hand or with a stand mixer until you achieve a smooth, supple, and slightly sticky dough."
   },
   {
    "titre": "First Rise",
    "detail": "Form into a ball, cover with a damp towel, and let rise in a warm place until the dough doubles in volume. The dough must DOUBLE in volume in a warm spot (77°F, oven off with the light on)."
   },
   {
    "titre": "Shape the Buns",
    "detail": "Gently deflate the dough. Divide into equal portions of 90-100g. Shape into smooth balls by folding the dough underneath. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, spacing them well apart."
   },
   {
    "titre": "Second Rise",
    "detail": "Cover and let rise until the buns have puffed up nicely. The dough must DOUBLE in volume in a warm spot (77°F, oven off with the light on)."
   },
   {
    "titre": "Egg Wash and Garnish",
    "detail": "Preheat the oven to 180°C. Gently brush the buns with milk (or diluted egg yolk). Sprinkle with sesame seeds. Allow at least 10 minutes at the correct temperature for proper cooking to begin."
   },
   {
    "titre": "Bake",
    "detail": "Bake at 180°C. The buns are ready when they're well-browned and sound hollow when tapped. As soon as they come out of the oven, brush with melted butter for a shiny appearance. Use convection heat for even baking."
   }
